race.comment: GLASTONBURY GIRL (6) couldn't have been more impressive when winning her Maiden at this track (slow surface) by 1.5L over 1400m. Settled back and had to cover plenty of ground before finishing over the top of them. Will be fitter again and the mile is sure to suit. In a smart Sydney yard and she can take the next step. MR MAGNIFICENCE (3) is a local third-up off two solid runs at Albury. He can position forward and won't have to improve much to fight out the finish. HELIGAN (8) was well held last time out in the tougher Geelong Classic won by Azazel over 2200m at Geelong. Ran a decent figure when narrowly beaten this trip from the speed at Moruya prior. He comes back home on a 12-day return, so must be pleasing. PROPHET'S PROMISE (4) is proving hard to catch but has ability and it wouldn't surprise to see him running into the money.
